name: oyster mushroom
note:
Gently pat with remove any moisture. Trim off hard stem at the base of each clump. Separate large caps, leave whole if small.
8oz mushroom, 4t olive oil, 2 garlic, 4t butter, salt and pepper.
Heat olive oil in large skillet over med high heat. Spread mushrooms out in single layer. Cook undisturbed for 3-5 min til browned. Stir, then cook another 3-5 min til all browned. (Do not crowd or overlap. Cook multiple batches if needed.)
Add butter, garlic, thyme to skillet. Reduce heat to low. Cook 5-6 min, spooning butter over mushrooms til dark brown and slightly crispy.
Or, bake 8oz (1.5" pieces) with 1T olive oil at 425F for 20-25 min (stirring halfway).
